                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8–2244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-22T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 22, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 22—8: 57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1446. Tihwa telegraphs that Chu Shao-liang arrived there 15th (ReEmbtel 1419,
                    August 16, 2 p.m.) and that situation that time seemed less tense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
